The paper focuses on the task of semantic labeling of source code, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The use of deep convolutional neural networks for this task also suggests a potential overlap with the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of maintaining up-to-date representations of new programming languages and libraries, which relates to the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of Github as a source of unlabeled source code documents, which could potentially involve computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for analyzing code snippets.
